    <div class="container">
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> A. General Provisions </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body">
            <p>The honors from Pre-Elementary, Elementary and High school will be designated as WITH HIGHEST HONORS, WITH HIGH
              HONORS, and WITH HONORS.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>All candidates for honors should have at least one year residency in the school including the current school
                year.
              </li>
              <li>They should have completed the entire course in not more than the number of curriculum years as prescribed
                by the Department of Education.</li>
              <li>They should not have failed any subject including non-credits subjects required by the Department of Education.</li>
              <li>Based on the average of the grades in the first three grading periods of the current school year, the pupil/student
                must have an average of 90% or better in the BEC/SEC Learning Areas, must not have a grade lower than 80%
                in any subject during the last three grading periods of the current school year.</li>
              <li>Fourth year honor students must attain a final rating of P (passed) in CAT.</li>
              <li>The candidate must have conducted himself/herself in conformity with school rules and regulations.</li>
              <li>Honors will be announced at least five (5) days before the graduation.</li>
              <li>Any pupils or students who will get the following general average will be declared honors:</li>
              <ul>
                <li>90-92 - with honors</li>
                <li>93-95 - with high honors</li>
                <li>96 and above - with highest honors</li>
              </ul>
              <li>For Kinder III, Grade Six and Fourth Year levels, the valedictorian and salutatorian will be determined by
                using the following: Quality Factors in Choosing the Valedictorian and Salutatorian
              </li>
              <ul>
                <li>CO-CURRICULAR-the sum of co-curricular ranking for the school year based on the activity checklist accomplished
                  by the candidates under the supervision of the class adviser.</li>
                <li>CHARACTER-rank based on the combined assessment of the subject teachers and adviser of the candidate using
                  the character checklist.</li>
              </ul>
              <li>The final rank shall be the sum of the two quality factors multiplied by their respective weights. The first
                and second in rank will be declared valedictorian and salutatorian respectively.</li>
            </ul>

          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-12">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
          <div class="panel-heading" style="text-align:center;">
            <h4>
              <a> B. Breaking Ties </a>
            </h4>
          </div>
          <div class="panel-body" align="center">
            <p>In case of a tie for Salutatorian and Valedictorian, evaluation shall go down to the next lower grade or year
              level. For example, if there is a tie for a fourth year candidate, then the third year grades shall be evaluated.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-12">
